parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
often when the brake pedal is depressed
and may continue to accelerate even when the brake pedal is fully engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
or the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly repair or replace the rear suspension arms can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: and difficulty in aligning the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Master Cylinder and Concentric Slave Cylinder Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder and concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause the vehicle to lose power, vibrate, or make a loud noise, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Growling noise from the rear differential

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to slip, jerk, or hesitate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
